            <title>[GROOVY-1967] When assigned to a local variable or attribute, a closure with named parameters throws a verify error</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-1967</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When assigned to a local variable or attribute, a closure with named parameters throws a verify error.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, if the closure is called directly upon creation (i.e. without intermediate assignment to a variable), then the call works without problems.&lt;br/&gt;
The same holds true if in a script the Binding is used to store the closure reference instead of a variable.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here is a test case. The commented test methods throw the verify error.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;class ClosureNamedParameters extends GroovyTestCase {&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;//	void testClosureAsLocalVar() {&lt;br/&gt;
//	    def local = &lt;/p&gt;
{ Map params -&amp;gt;
//	        params.x * params.y
//	    }&lt;br/&gt;
//		assert local(x : 2, y : 3) == 6&lt;br/&gt;
//	}&lt;br/&gt;
	void testClosureDirectly() {&lt;br/&gt;
	    assert { Map params -&amp;gt;
	        params.x * params.y
	    }(x : 2, y : 3) == 6&lt;br/&gt;
	}&lt;br/&gt;
//	def attribute&lt;br/&gt;
//	void testClosureAsAttribute() {&lt;br/&gt;
//	    attribute = { Map params -&amp;gt;//	        params.x * params.y//	    }
&lt;p&gt;//		assert attribute(x : 2, y : 3) == 6&lt;br/&gt;
//	}&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;</description>
